  "body": "I suddenly get the following error on running unit-tests in my 1-years-old hardhat based project using Upgradables:\r\n\r\n> error TS2305: Module '\"hardhat\"' has no exported member 'upgrades'.\r\n\r\nThis happens when importing:\r\n\r\n`import {ethers, upgrades} from 'hardhat';`\r\n\r\nThe difference between my last successful run and the latest attempt is that I have installed node_modules from scratch.\r\nAccording to what I [read about](https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/openzeppelin-upgrades-step-by-step-tutorial-for-hardhat/3580) how to use Hardhat with OpenZeppelin Upgradables, these libraries should provide everything:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  \"devDependencies\": {\r\n    \"@nomicfoundation/hardhat-network-helpers\": \"^1.0.6\",\r\n    \"@nomiclabs/buidler\": \"^1.4.8\",\r\n    \"@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers\": \"^2.1.1\",\r\n    \"@nomiclabs/hardhat-etherscan\": \"^3.0.3\",\r\n    \"@nomiclabs/hardhat-waffle\": \"^2.0.3\",\r\n    \"@openzeppelin/hardhat-upgrades\": \"^1.21.0\",\r\n    \"@openzeppelin/test-helpers\": \"^0.5.15\",\r\n```\r\n\r\nApparently, the `upgrades`-object has been removed from hardhat. \r\n\r\nIs there any replacement?\r\n",
